snippet.title: Crowd Stops in Awe as 4-Year-Old Sings ‘Goodness of God’
snippet.description:
When Karolina Protsenko introduced her 4-year-old brother Nicholas to the crowd, no one expected what happened next. Nicholas sat at the piano and began to sing Goodness of God with such pure emotion that the crowd stopped in awe.
Some started singing along, others just stood still — many said they had never experienced anything like it. 🎹 Goodness of God cover by 4-year-old Nicholas Protsenko and his sister Karolina is a truly beautiful moment of sibling harmony, worship, and talent.

✨ Watch as this street performance melts hearts and inspires everyone who hears it.

💬 Comment below — how did this performance touch you?

🚢 Titanic 2 

A century after the real-life disaster and over 25 years after James Cameron’s Titanic broke box office records, a new generation is about to experience the legendary romance and tragedy — this time with a fresh twist. Rumor has it that a reimagined version of Titanic is in the works, with Timothée Chalamet and Zendaya set to star as star-crossed lovers aboard the ill-fated ship.

The project, tentatively titled Titanic, is said to be less of a straight remake and more of a “reinterpretation” — blending historical drama, romance, and a modern narrative structure designed to resonate with younger audiences while honoring the grandeur of the original film.

Insiders claim that this new Titanic will weave together two timelines: the doomed 1912 voyage and a present-day investigation by a young historian (played by Zendaya) uncovering a mysterious diary linked to a passenger named Jack Dawson — here reimagined and played by Timothée Chalamet.

Feel free to express your thoughts on this exciting project by leaving a comment below.

snippet.title: Good Boy - Official Trailer | HD | IFC Films
snippet.description:
Indy, a loyal golden-brown retriever, follows his owner Todd to an aging farmhouse tucked deep in the countryside. But the walls whisper, the shadows breathe, and something unseen has already claimed the place. Todd is blind to the horrors curling around them — but Indy can see. Through the dog’s eyes, the world twists into a nightmare of flickering visions and lurking shapes. Bound by unshakable loyalty, Indy stands between his human and the darkness, ready to face the things no one else can see.
